item.description:
[1:1] An oracle: the word of Yahweh to Israel by Malachi.
[1:2] &ldquo;I have loved you,&rdquo; says Yahweh. Yet you say, &ldquo;How have you loved us?&rdquo; &ldquo;Wasn&rsquo;t Esau Jacob&rsquo;s brother?&rdquo; says Yahweh, &ldquo;Yet I loved Jacob;
[1:3] but Esau I hated, and made his mountains a desolation, and gave his heritage to the jackals of the wilderness.&rdquo;
[1:4] Whereas Edom says, &ldquo;We are beaten down, but we will return and build the waste places;&rdquo; thus says Yahweh of Hosts, &ldquo;They shall build, but I will throw down; and men will call them &lsquo;The Wicked Land,&rsquo; even the people against whom Yahweh shows wrath forever.
